      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Ultimate Combat pg. 162</em></p><h3 class=\"framing\">Statistics</h3><p><strong>Cost</strong> 6,000 gp <strong>Weight</strong> -</p><p><strong>Damage</strong> 6d6; <strong>Critical</strong> x4; <strong>Range</strong> 100 ft.; <strong>Type</strong> B and P</p><p><strong>Crew</strong> 2; <strong>Aim</strong> 1; <strong>Load</strong> 3; <strong>Speed</strong> 10 ft.</p><p><strong>Category</strong> Direct-Fire (Large); <strong>Proficiency</strong> Siege Engine</p><h3 class=\"framing\">Description</h3><p>Cannons are crafted of metal-some are cast in one piece, others welded with iron bands-and mounted either in the ground or on wooden frames. Cannons use black powder to propel their projectiles with great force. A cannon has a misfire range of 1 (20 feet). Cannons have a hardness of 10 and 70 hit points. Cannon balls cost 30 gp each and weigh 25 pounds.</p>",
